		<section id="about-our-server">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>About Our Server</h2>
        <p>Welcome to our FiveM server! Here's what you need to know about our server:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>vMenu:</strong> Our server utilizes the vMenu script to provide players with a range of administrative and customization options. With vMenu, you can easily manage your player settings, spawn vehicles, teleport, and much more.</li>
            <li><strong>FivePD:</strong> Experience the thrill of law enforcement roleplay with our FivePD script. Play as a police officer, sheriff's deputy, or other emergency service role and immerse yourself in realistic patrol scenarios, investigations, and traffic stops.</li>
            <li><strong>Police Radio:</strong> Communicate effectively with other law enforcement personnel using our integrated police radio system. Coordinate responses, request backup, and stay informed about ongoing incidents in real-time.</li>
            <li><strong>Active Staff:</strong> Our dedicated staff team is committed to ensuring a positive and enjoyable gaming experience for all players. If you have any questions, concerns, or need assistance, feel free to reach out to our active staff members for help.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
		</section>

        <section id="rules" class="alt-bg">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Rules</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Respectful Behavior:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Treat all players and staff members with respect and courtesy.</li>
                            <li>Avoid using offensive language, discriminatory remarks, or engaging in harassment of any kind.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Roleplay Guidelines:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Engage in realistic and immersive roleplay interactions.</li>
                            <li>Follow server-specific roleplay rules and guidelines to enhance the overall gaming experience.</li>
                            <li>Use appropriate character names and avoid breaking character unless necessary.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>vMenu Usage:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Use vMenu responsibly and avoid abusing its features.</li>
                            <li>Refrain from spamming vehicle spawning, teleportation, or other administrative commands.</li>
                            <li>Do not use vMenu to disrupt gameplay, spawn excessive vehicles, or cause server instability.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>FivePD Gameplay:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Follow the server's law enforcement guidelines and procedures when playing as a police officer or other emergency service role.</li>
                            <li>Respect the chain of command and cooperate with other players and staff members during patrol sessions.</li>
                            <li>Do not engage in excessive force, abuse of authority, or other misconduct while playing as a law enforcement officer.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Server Rules:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Familiarize yourself with the server's rules and regulations, including those specific to vMenu and FivePD usage.</li>
                            <li>Adhere to server-specific guidelines regarding character creation, vehicle modifications, server economy, etc.</li>
                            <li>Report any rule violations or suspicious behavior to server staff promptly.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Communication:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Use in-game chat, voice chat, or Discord channels responsibly.</li>
                            <li>Avoid spamming, excessive mic chatter, or disrupting communication channels.</li>
                            <li>Communicate effectively with other players, especially during roleplay scenarios and emergency situations.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Community Engagement:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Participate in community events, roleplay scenarios, and server activities.</li>
                            <li>Contribute positively to the server's community by helping other players, providing constructive feedback, and engaging in roleplay interactions.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Reporting Issues:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Report any bugs, glitches, or server-related issues to server staff using the appropriate channels.</li>
                            <li>Provide detailed information and evidence when reporting rule violations, suspected cheaters, or disruptive behavior.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </section>


